page.title: 02LIVING IN ENGLEFIELD GREEN
page.content: When I moved in Englefield Green in 1977 they were starting to build Schroeder Court,where my mother works. There was'nt such thing as the Corby Drive Estate.There are some of the things that have changed.ST Jude's Rd has been made bigger and they have built the new estate.The old ST Judes school has been pulled down and Englefield Close has been built.The laundrette has been made into two shops and lots of roads have been re_surfaced.Englefield Green is all on top of a hill.There is a gap between us and Old Windsor and in that gap is where the pop singer Elton John lives. Over the other side of Englefield Green,down Wick Lane,there is the entrance to the park.Which is near the Totem Pole and the Obelisk.
